args:
Elisanne, Edward, and Althemia all dress up
as vampires, which allows them to defeat the
fiends that attacked the Halidom. Curious as to
their attackers' motives, the party heads out into
the surrounding environs in search of answers.
Wooo! We got everything we needed for\nthe costumes. Easy peasy, right?
We got, what? Enough to make costumes\nfor maybe three people?
Yes, and I imagine Althemia should be\nfinishing them up about now.
Indeed, she said she could be finished\nwith them some time around noon, master.
Plus, we found some'a them stolen treats\nwhile we were out there! That's a fine\npiece'a luck if ya ask me.
If we keep gettin' 'em back like that,\nour little Sweet Retreat will be sittin'\npretty.
Come, everyone. Let us review the plan.
First, Althemia, Edward, and I will\napproach the fiends while in costume.
Then we will drive them to the location\nwhere {player_name}'s team has\nprepared an ambush.
Then we just have to finish them off.\nAny questions?
Thank you, Althemia. We will get changed\nat once.
Hmm... Interesting. These appear to be\npatterned after vampires.
The fiends from legend who survived by\ndrinking human blood? I remember\nreading about them when I was young.
Hold up a sec there, Jeeves.\nYou use blades?
But of course. Any butler worth his salt can\nuse myriad weapons.
Still, I must say, equipping a blade\ncertainly does get my blood pumping.
For starters, I of course feel the desire to\nfeed the weapon the blood of my enemies.
Additionally, blades make much better\ncorrectional tools than staves when it\ncomes to dealing with time wasters.
...Come now, why are you trembling?\nI speak in jest, of course.
Uh, pretty sure yer eyes were tellin' a\ndifferent story there. Think maybe I'll just\nback away now...
Oh wow! She looks like what cute wants\nto be when it grows up.
It really is a wonderful costume.
What?! Um, I, oh... Er...\nI don't need your flattery!
You probably don't even think it looks like\na vampire, right?!
I had that same thought when I was\nmaking the costumes.
But then I figured that since I had to make\nthem, I might as well go with a design that\nI wanted to wear! ...Or something.
I mean, come ON! The whole ＂vampires\nare beautiful aristocrats＂ thing is\nCOMPLETELY played out.
I can't argue with you there. Plus you\nlook pretty cute as a vampire.
Enough of this gum-flapping! Hurry up and\nget out here already, Elisanne!
This...this is SHAMEFUL! How could you\neven THINK I would don such a garment?!
You must set aside your personal feelings,\nMadam Elisanne. The plan will be in\ngrave danger of going awry otherwise.
Y-yeah! Stop complaining and put it on!
I...I suppose you're right. And yet...
Elly, if you don't like wearing the costume,\nmaybe I could wear it instead.
What?! No! You DEFINITELY cannot do that!
It's no problem. I don't want to make a\ncomrade do something he or she isn't\ncomfortable with.
Your Highness, you CANNOT wear this.\n...Ugh. Oh, very well. It seems I have\nlittle choice in this matter.
Cleo? Don't. Say. Another word.\nI'm just as perplexed by this entire\naffair as you are.
Did vampires TRULY dress like this,\nAlthemia? It's so...showy!
How is a blood-drinking creature supposed\nto creep about in the dark while wearing\nsuch an obvious outfit?!
Of course, it IS rather cute, but...\nIt's just not...for me...
W-well, according to folklore, vampires\ntook on an appearance that would help\nthem seduce their prey.
Hey, they say anyone can look good in the\nright outfit, yeah? ...Although in yer case,\nya look kinda pumpkin-y.
Oh, fine. Let's just get this over with.\nAlthemia, Edward—let's go!
The plan worked! They're headed your way.
Why are you just standing there?\nYou mustn't be so careless!
Sorry—and thanks for the assist.\nCan you cover my flank?
Protecting one's master is a butler's\nsolemn duty. Leave it to me.
Althemia's costumes proved their worth, and the\ngroup took out the fiends one after the other.
You guys were GREAT! I don't think you\nlet even a single one escape.
These costumes were a big help, too.
Of course they were a big help—they\nwere made by ME, after all!
M-more importantly, now that we've driven\noff the fiends, this is our chance.
We must determine why they continue to\nswarm the castle.
Good thinking. Otherwise, another horde\nis sure to come around before long.
Let's get to investigating—everyone keep\nyour eyes peeled for anything suspicious.
